Package: BTSPAS
Version: 2015.0702
Date: 2015-07-02
Title: Bayesian Time-Strat. Population Analysis
Author: Carl J Schwarz <cschwarz@stat.sfu.ca> and
	Simon J Bonner <simon.bonner@uky.edu>
Maintainer: Carl J Schwarz <cschwarz@stat.sfu.ca>
Note: See http://stackoverflow.com/questions/28351030/ggplotgrob-function-is-not-found-when-i-use-it-in-a-package-which-imports-ggplot on why ggplot2 must be in Depends field
Note: See bottom of http://stackoverflow.com/questions/29062766/store-output-from-gridextragrid-arrange-into-an-object on why gridExtra must be depends field
Depends: ggplot2, gridExtra
Imports: actuar, coda, graphics, grDevices, plyr, rjags, R2OpenBUGS, splines, stats, utils
Suggests: BRugs
SystemRequirements: JAGS
Description: Provides advanced Bayesian methods to estimate
	     abundance and run-timing from temporally-stratified
	     Petersen mark-recapture experiments. Methods include
	     hierarchical modelling of the capture probabilities
  	     and spline smoothing of the daily run size. This version 
	     uses JAGS to sample from the posterior distribution.
License: GPL (>=2)
URL: http://www.stat.sfu.ca/~cschwarz/Consulting/Trinity/Phase2


